The paper is about dense robotic mapping, which is a subfield of robotics and computer vision. The use of Bayesian models and machine learning techniques also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper's focus on semantic mapping and the use of semantic classes suggests a connection to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
